Wash and dry all produce.

Slice @fresh mozzarella{4%ounce} and @Roma tomato{1} into ¼-inch-thick rounds. Season tomato with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Halve @ciabatta bread{2}. Toast until golden, if desired.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @pesto{2%ounce} and @mayonnaise{1%ounce}; spread onto cut sides of ciabatta. Fill with tomato, @prosciutto{2%ounce}, and mozzarella.

Cut sandwiches on a diagonal.

> Making a great sandwich is an art form. Dismiss the dramatics—when you get it right, there's really nothing better! This one's got crusty bread, creamy pesto mayo, salty prosciutto, ripe tomato, and mozz. Put it together at the office or be your own best friend and whip it up before you leave for work. When noon rolls around, you'll be looking at the office fridge with heart eyes.